<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,517,686,712]" box="[151,517,686,712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,517,686,712]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Aurivillius, 1925" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1925" box="[151,517,686,712]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Xanthodisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,517,686,712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,303,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Xanthodisca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius" box="[309,517,686,712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="245" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1925) 9. Familie: Hesperidae. In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Eine systematische Bearbeitung der bis jetzt bekannten Gross-schmetterlinge. In Verbindung mit namhaftesten Fachmannern herausgegeben. Die Africanischen Tagfelter. Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart, pp. 505 - 588." type="book chapter" year="1925">
Aurivillius, 
<number box="[458,517,686,712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1925.0">1925</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,757,1250]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
This genus was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius" box="[505,711,757,782]" pageId="18" pageNumber="245" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1925) 9. Familie: Hesperidae. In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Eine systematische Bearbeitung der bis jetzt bekannten Gross-schmetterlinge. In Verbindung mit namhaftesten Fachmannern herausgegeben. Die Africanischen Tagfelter. Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart, pp. 505 - 588." type="book chapter" year="1925">
Aurivillius (
<number box="[644,702,757,782]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1925.0">1925</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Hewitson" authorityName="Hewitson" box="[763,1103,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Astictopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vibius">
<emphasis box="[763,987,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Astictopterus vibius</emphasis>
Hewitson
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1807" box="[1163,1432,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rega">
<emphasis box="[1163,1332,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Pamphila rega</emphasis>
Mabille
</taxonomicName>
, which at that time was considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[739,806,793,818]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Astictopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vibius">
<emphasis box="[739,806,793,818]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">vibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Up until then, 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1059,793,818]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Astictopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vibius">
<emphasis box="[992,1059,793,818]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">vibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been treated as a species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,291,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Pardaleodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[361,515,830,854]" pageId="18" pageNumber="246" refString="Evans, W. H. (1937) A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History), London, 212 pp., 30 pls." type="book" year="1937">
Evans (
<number box="[449,507,830,854]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName box="[659,799,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Xanthodisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[659,799,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Xanthodisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be closely allied to 
<emphasis box="[1077,1226,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicName box="[1077,1221,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pardaleodes</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Evans added two species to the genus: 
<taxonomicName box="[387,618,865,890]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astrape">
<emphasis box="[387,618,865,890]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Pardaleodes astrape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from West and central Africa and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1807" box="[1002,1266,865,890]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariel">
<emphasis box="[1002,1170,865,890]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Pamphila ariel</emphasis>
Mabille
</taxonomicName>
, a Madagascan endemic. 
<bibRefCitation author="Carcasson" box="[261,459,902,926]" pageId="18" pageNumber="245" refString="Carcasson, R. H. (1981) Collins Handguide to the Butterflies of Africa. Collins, London, 188 pp." type="book" year="1981">
Carcasson (
<number box="[393,451,902,926]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[517,749,901,926]" pageId="18" pageNumber="245" refString="Ackery, P. R., Smith, C. R. &amp; Vane-Wright, R. I. (Eds.) (1995) Carcasson's African Butterflies. An annotated catalogue of the Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea of the Afrotropical Region. CSIRO Publications, Melbourne, 803 pp." type="book">
Ackery 
<emphasis box="[608,658,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[682,740,901,926]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName box="[842,942,901,926]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Astictopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vibius">
<emphasis box="[842,942,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">X. vibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1807" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1807" box="[1000,1081,902,925]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rega">
<emphasis box="[1000,1081,902,925]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">X. rega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct species, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen" pageId="18" pageNumber="246" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. 2 Vols. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Larsen (
<number box="[159,218,937,962]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
confirmed that they overlap in distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[743,863,938,962]" name="Cameroon" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,757,1250]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
The late T.B. Larsen (pers. comm. 
<number box="[597,655,973,998]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="2015.0">2015</number>
) re-examined the members of the genus, and concluded that 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1807" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1807" box="[1350,1436,973,998]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariel">
<emphasis box="[1350,1436,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">X. ariel</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably belongs to one of the Madagascan endemic genera (
<taxonomicName box="[840,934,1010,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Perrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[840,934,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Perrotia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1049,1010,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Miraja" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[971,1049,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Miraja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[1171,1255,1010,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astrape">
<emphasis box="[1171,1255,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">astrape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not related to any other genus, so he planned to describe new genus to hold it. The food plants of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1807" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1807" box="[1101,1154,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariel">
<emphasis box="[1101,1154,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">ariel</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unknown but Larsen suggests they will be found to be bamboos, whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[735,832,1081,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Astictopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vibius">
<emphasis box="[735,832,1081,1106]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">X. vibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1807" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1807" box="[885,967,1082,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rega">
<emphasis box="[885,967,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">X. rega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feed on 
<taxonomicName box="[1061,1200,1082,1106]" class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="Aframomum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1061,1200,1082,1106]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Aframomum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName box="[1266,1428,1081,1106]" class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Zingiberaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[198,313,1118,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astrape">
<emphasis box="[198,313,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">X. astrape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feeds on 
<taxonomicName box="[421,567,1118,1141]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Marantaceae</taxonomicName>
, and is treated below in the section on 
<taxonomicName box="[1001,1144,1118,1141]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Marantaceae</taxonomicName>
feeders. Contrary to what 
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius" box="[151,356,1153,1178]" pageId="18" pageNumber="245" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1925) 9. Familie: Hesperidae. In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Eine systematische Bearbeitung der bis jetzt bekannten Gross-schmetterlinge. In Verbindung mit namhaftesten Fachmannern herausgegeben. Die Africanischen Tagfelter. Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart, pp. 505 - 588." type="book chapter" year="1925">
Aurivillius (
<number box="[290,348,1153,1178]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1925.0">1925</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[415,568,1154,1178]" pageId="18" pageNumber="246" refString="Evans, W. H. (1937) A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History), London, 212 pp., 30 pls." type="book" year="1937">
Evans (
<number box="[501,560,1154,1178]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
thought, 
<taxonomicName box="[679,819,1153,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Xanthodisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[679,819,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Xanthodisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1247,1153,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1107,1247,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Pardaleodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a grass-feeding genus treated in Cock &amp; Congdon (
<number box="[571,632,1190,1214]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" value="2014.0">2014</number>
), rather it shows clear affinities with the other Zingiberaceae-feeders treated here, especially 
<taxonomicName box="[415,510,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Semalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[415,510,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Semalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(above).
</paragraph>
